Sure, I wouldn't be going over first wave, and I would more likely than not be floating over the horizon on a hospital ship, waiting in the O.R. where I work for the casualties to start rolling in.<br>
I knew that a war in the span of my enlistment was a possibility, however remote, but it still sort of scares me, to be frank. Especially one in Iraq. <br>
The reason we would be going over there is mainly due to the fact that Saddam has not been fulfilling his end of the treaties he signed back in '91(or whenever, I was only in jr. high then, and wasn't paying too much attention..) to get us to stop pounding his shit. He more likely than not has C/B/R weapons that he should not have. <br>
If it comes to rolling troops into Iraq for the SOLE purpose of removing him forcefully for his noncompliance, I think he will not hesistate to blast off as many of those weapons as possible. I would not doubt that he would like as many casualties as possible, US or otherwise (most likely a good chunk of his own civilians, he has in the past...). <br>
Sure, I've had all kinds of C/B/R training, but only a fool wouldn't be a little scared. C/B/R agents are scary shit. All the classroom training in the world can't fully prepare you for that. Most of that shit will either kill you or seriously fuck you up. Fast. <br>
Dunno. Looks like there's a job to do. I don't like it much, but what I do or don't like doesn't matter much, if they order me to do.<br>
Guess I should get my Seabag in order. May actually need it.<br>
